<p>Make one commit per logical change</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">git log</code> to see which files have been changed in each commit</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">git clone</code> to download the whole repository</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">git config --global color.ui auto</code></p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">git checkout id</code>: go back to a commit</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">git checkout branch_name</code>: most recent commit</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">git diff</code> with no arguments: compare current state with most recent commit</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">git reset Â­Â­--hard</code> to get rid of uncommitted changes</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">git commit -Â­a -Â­m "Commit message"</code> commit all changes</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">git reflog</code>: commits that recently checked out</p>
